<TEXT>
A bus plunged off a roadside cliff and down a 
steep ravine in the high Andes killing 15 passengers and injuring 
four police said Tuesday 
The crash occurred Monday afternoon near the town of Pallasca in 
Ancash state about 300 miles northeast of Lima police said The 
bus had started from Lima and only had 15 miles more to go before 
reaching its destination the town of Conchucos police said 
It was not known how many people were aboard the privately owned 
bus 
Police were investigating the cause of the accident 
Heavy rains usually weaken Perus mainly dirt and gravel 
mountain roads this time of year causing more accidents 
</TEXT>
